Despite reported cancellation by the National Working Committee (NWC), Dr Ifeanyichukwu Odii was on Sunday night declared winner of Ebonyi Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) governorship primary conducted at the Secretariat in Abakaliki. The Electoral Panel Chairman, Olalekan Rotimi, who declared the results, said Odii polled highest number of valid votes to defeat other five contestants. According to him, Odi got 349 votes while his closest rival Christian Usolor got nine votes and the duo of Chukwuma Nwazunku and Augustine Nwazunku got one vote each. Rotimi added that Emmanuel Ezeh got one vote while Andrew Sunday got six votes respectively. “Therefore, I, Olalekan Rotimi having been conferred with the power to chair this panel hereby declare Ifeanyichukwu Odi, having polled the total highest number of valid votes and having met all the requirements, winner of the primary election.   Lagos partners Finland to boost schools’ programme     Adopt Onu as consensus candidate, group begs APC     Forum declares support for Tinubu, Sanwo-Olu   “The exercise was counted openly and witnessed by agents of the aspirants, officials of the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) and other stakeholders,” Rotimi said. Odii thanked the delegates and the party for electing him to carry its flag and promised to lead PDP to victory in the 2023 governorship election in Ebonyi. He pledged to work with every member of the party to achieve victory. Factional chairman of the party, Silas Onu, commended the delegates for peaceful and orderly conduct in the exercise. A faction of the party loyal to Chief Tochukwu Okorie had at a news conference in Abakaliki on Sunday announced that the primar had been cancelled on the directive of the national leadership of the PDP. The faction noted that the date for the primary election would be announced in due course.